incorporating new stuff into rails - bootstrap, grayscale, other css files

fontawesome is a gem
anything that says glyphicons is provided by Bootstrap
 you can use trial and error to integrate major libraries that have gems
 step 1) identify what needs to be integrated
 step 2) integrate gems

 put the gem in gem file
 gem 'simple_form'
 gem 'font-awesome-sass', '~> 4.4.0'

 Bundle

 create custom.css.scss in assets/stylesheets
 import "bootstrap";
 @import "font-awesome-sprockets";
 @import "font-awesome"

go to grayscale folder and find index.html
copy entire page into app/static_pages/test.html.erb
restart server

step 3) integrate unique parts of grayscale into our app

copy from grayscale folder /css/grayscale.css into stylesheets folder

step 4) add grayscale css and integrate grayscale css

integrate each css file to pipeline
in application.css
*= require_tree .
*= require grayscale
*= require_self
*/
restart server to test our file

