 step 5) now we need to integrate javascript libraries to application
 copy 2 files from js / grayscale and jquery.easing.min into assets/javascripts

 in application.js
 //= require jquery
 //= require jquery_ujs
 //= require jquery.easing.min
 //= require bootstrap-sprockets
 //= require grayscale
 //= require turbolinks
 //= require_tree .
oder matters because some libraries are dependent on others, so they need to be loaded in a specific order

in test.htmlremove script files at bottom
and delete font-awesome in custom font-size

now we do stuff with the font - go to google fonts
make sure you import it after checking off the ones you want
this provides the code to import it
import the code to custom.css.scss in stylesheets (section 3)
and also the code to integrate it into your css (section 4)
@import "bootstrap";
@import "font-awesome-sprockets";
@import "font-awesome";

/* Fonts */
@import url(https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lora:400,400italic,700,700italic);
/* will only make it available for ?? */

@import url(https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Montserrat:400,700);

.lora_font {
font-family: 'Lora', serif;
}
.montserrat_font {
font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
}

by doing so, we can now delete the fonts stuff from test.html



